<HEADLINE> AP Top News at 1 a.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tuesday, June 6, 2000
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Strong Quake Shakes Central Turkey
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   ANKARA, Turkey (AP) -- A strong earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of
5.9 shook central Turkey early Tuesday, the Istanbul-based Kandilli Observatory
said. There was no immediate information on whether it caused any injuries or
damage. The epicenter was the town of Cerkez in Cankiri province, 60 miles north
of the capital, Ankara, Kandilli said. The quake, which lasted about 30 seconds,
was felt in Ankara, its environs and along the Black Sea coast.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Sierra Leone Diamond Embargo Mulled
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   UNITED NATIONS (AP) -- Britain is proposing that the U.N. Security Council
