<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 02:05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flames Poised To Hire Button as GM  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CALGARY, Alberta(AP) -- Craig Button, one of the architects of
the defending Stanley Cup champion Dallas Stars, was expected to be
introduced today as the new general manager of the Calgary Flames.
</P>
<P>
   The Flames called a news conference for noon EDT to make a
''major'' announcement concerning the organization's management.
</P>
<P>
   TSN reported Monday night that the Flames were going to hire
Button, the Stars' director of player personnel, as GM.
</P>
<P>
   The Calgary Sun said sources confirmed that Button will be
hired.
</P>
<P>
   Button, 37, has spent the last 12 seasons with Dallas, two in
his current role and the previous six as the team's director of
scouting.
</P>
<P>
   The Montreal native has deep roots in hockey. His late father,
Jack, was an NHL general manager; his mother, Bridget, worked for
Punch Imlach and the Toronto Maple Leafs; and his brother, Tod, is
a scout for the Flames.
</P>
<P>
   Former Leafs coach Mike Murphy was considered a front-runner for
the GM's job, but Murphy said Monday night after arriving at the
Stanley Cup finals that he was told by the Flames he wasn't getting
the post.
</P>
<P>
   Calgary Flames co-owner Harley Hotchkiss said last week that the
process of hiring a new general manager was in its ''final
stages.''
</P>
<P>
   According to the TSN report, Lanny McDonald, currently Calgary's
vice president of corporate development, would become Button's boss
as the team's new vice president of hockey operations.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, ESPN hockey analyst Barry Melrose speculated that
Roger Neilson, the out-of-favor coach in Philadelphia, will become
the Flames' new coach.
</P>
<P>
   However, Neilson said Monday he knew nothing of any such
interest.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's news to me,'' he said. ''If the decision goes down that I
will not be head coach of the Flyers, then certainly I'll be asking
permission to talk to other teams, and certainly the Flames will be
one of them.
</P>
<P>
   ''They haven't even named a general manager, yet. I have no
knowledge of this.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
