<HEADLINE> Carrey Had a Crush on Zellweger  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Hot Hollywood celebrity couple Jim Carrey and
Renee Zellweger didn't experience love at first, or second, or even
third sight.
</P>
<P>
   It wasn't until after they finished filming the upcoming ''Me,
Myself &AMP; Irene'' that Zellweger finally succumbed to the smitten
Carrey's charms.
</P>
<P>
   While making the movie, ''he became very important to me as a
friend,'' the 31-year-old Zellweger said in the July issue of
Vanity Fair. ''I mean, we had had some fun together.''
</P>
<P>
   Carrey, 38, had met Zellweger over dinner at a mutual friend's
house about two years ago. He fell for her during filming, but
Zellweger's affections grew a bit slower.
</P>
<P>
   ''I was there for work,'' Zellweger said. ''All I know is that
once he was gone I missed him. Badly. So maybe I was falling in
love.''
</P>
