<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded
heavily Tuesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Bestfoods, up $6.188 to $69.188
Unilever NV, up 87.5 cents to $51.25
</P>
<P>
   Bestfoods, the maker of Hellman's mayonnaise and Skippy peanut
butter, accepted a $73 a share takeover offer from Anglo-Dutch
conglomerate Unilever NV. The deal put an end to speculation that
Bestfoods would pursue an acquisition of Campbell Soup Co.
</P>
<P>
Circuit City Group, down $12.625 to $39.50
</P>
<P>
   The company said gross profit margins for the first quarter will
be lower than previously forecast. Circuit City said sales of major
