</P>
<P>
   ABN Amro named the company a ''top pick.'' Altera, a leading
maker of programmable logic computer chips, has been encouraging
Wall Street analysts to raise their revenue estimates for the
current year.
</P>
<P>
drkoop.com Inc., up 93.75 cents at $2.719
</P>
<P>
   The struggling health-care Web site signed a two-year
sponsorship agreement with webofcare.com Inc., a virtual community
for caregivers. The agreement includes a fixed sponsorship payment
for drkoop.com, as well as a revenue-sharing agreement.
</P>
<P>
Electronics For Imaging Inc., down $10.813 at $23.938
</P>
<P>
   The company said it expects to post second-quarter earnings of
38 cents to 40 cents a share. Analysts had anticipated earnings of
51 cents a share. The company, a maker of hardware and software,
said orders received would not support analysts' estimates.
</P>
<P>
Puma Technology Inc., up $2.375 at $37
</P>
<P>
   The company introduced a Web-browsing product, Browse-It, which
provides Web access on Palm devices. Analysts said Puma may also be
preparing to announce deals with a U.S. portal and a foreign
Internet service provider.
</P>
