<HEADLINE> Tennesse Williams' House Sold  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KEY WEST, Fla. (AP) -- The former Key West ''shack'' of Tennessee
Williams has been sold to an Ohio couple for $1.15 million -- a
hefty sum that surprised the brother of the late playwright.
</P>
<P>
   ''Why, that was just a shack that floated over from Cuba,'' said
Dakin Williams, speaking from his home in Collinsville, Ill.
