<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bus Crash Kills 1, Injures 27  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KENTFORD, England (AP) -- A bus carrying 30 people collided with
a car, veered off the road and slammed into tree, killing the
driver and injuring about 27 others, one seriously, authorities
said.
</P>
<P>
   The passengers were taken to local hospitals, but most of their
injuries were minor, police said. One man was listed in critical
condition.
</P>
<P>
   The accident occurred shortly after 8 p.m. Tuesday when a
National Express bus traveling from London to Great Yarmouth hit a
car and left the road in Suffolk, about 60 miles northeast of
London, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities have not determined the cause of the crash.
</P>
</TEXT>
