<HEADLINE> Royals Sign First Round Pick  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- The Kansas City Royals signed
first-round draft pick Mike Stodolka on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Stodolka, 18, a 6-foot-2, 195-pound, left-handed pitcher, was
10-0 with a 0.67 ERA last season for Centennial High School in
Corona, Calif.
</P>
<P>
   ''Mike was very eager to sign and get his professional career
under way,'' said Terry Wetzel, the Royals scouting director.
</P>
<P>
   The fourth pick overall in the draft, Stodolka is the first high
school pitcher taken No. 1 by the Royals since 1977.
</P>
<P>
   Stodolka is scheduled to graduate from high school June 15.
</P>
</TEXT>
