<HEADLINE> Braves Draft Tony Gwynn's Son  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA (AP) -- Anthony Gwynn, the son of San Diego's Tony Gwynn,
was drafted Tuesday by the Atlanta Braves with the 1,000th pick of
the baseball draft.
</P>
<P>
   The younger Gwynn, a center fielder for Poway High School in
California, was taken in the 33rd round of the 50-round draft. He
will have to make a choice between turning pro or accepting a
scholarship offer from San Diego State, his father's alma mater.
</P>
<P>
   On Monday, the Braves took Pennsylvania high school shortstop
Aaron Herr, son of former Cardinals second baseman Tom Herr, with
the 40th pick. Herr hit .418 for Hempfield High School in
Lancaster, Pa.
</P>
</TEXT>
